<div class="min-h-screen bg-slate-50 py-16 px-4 font-sans">
  <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto">

    <!-- Back link -->
    <div class="mb-8">
      <%= link_to "← Back", root_path, class: "text-sm font-semibold text-slate-400 hover:text-indigo-600 transition-colors" %>
    </div>

    <!-- Header -->
    <div class="mb-10">
      <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-indigo-50 border border-indigo-100 rounded-full px-3 py-1 mb-4">
        <span class="text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-indigo-600">Legal</span>
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-slate-900 tracking-tight mb-3">Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-slate-400 font-medium">Last updated: March 25, 2026</p>
    </div>

    <!-- Card -->
    <div class="bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-sm border border-slate-100 divide-y divide-slate-100 overflow-hidden">

      <div class="px-8 py-7">
        <h2 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2">What data we access</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Homework Planner accesses your Google Classroom assignments, Google Calendar events, and Google Drive file metadata (read-only). We never modify, submit, or delete anything in your Google account.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-8 py-7">
        <h2 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2">How we use your data</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Your assignment data is used solely to generate your nightly study plan, time estimates, and scheduling. Your data is stored in our database to provide the service and is never shared with third parties.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-8 py-7">
        <h2 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2">Data storage</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Your data is stored on a secure, private server. Google OAuth tokens are encrypted at rest. We do not sell or share your personal information.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-8 py-7">
        <h2 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2">Deleting your data</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">You can request deletion of your account and all associated data by emailing <a href="mailto:jacetimm@gmail.com" class="font-semibold text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800 transition-colors">jacetimm@gmail.com</a>.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="px-8 py-7">
        <h2 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2">Data Protection &amp; Security</h2>

        <div class="space-y-5 text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Encryption in Transit</p>
            <p>All data transmitted between your browser and this app is encrypted using HTTPS/TLS. We do not serve any content over unencrypted HTTP.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Encryption at Rest</p>
            <p>Your Google OAuth access and refresh tokens are encrypted at rest in our database using Rails built-in encryption (ActiveRecord Encryption). API keys and secrets are stored using Rails encrypted credentials and are never stored in plaintext or version control.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Access Controls</p>
            <p>Our server is a privately hosted Raspberry Pi accessible only to the developer. No third parties have access to the server or database. Database credentials and server access are protected by SSH key authentication.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Data Minimization</p>
            <p>We only request Google API scopes strictly necessary for app functionality: reading your courses, assignments, submissions, and calendar. We do not request access to Google Drive, Gmail, or any other Google services.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Data Retention</p>
            <p>Cached assignment and calendar data is stored temporarily (up to 15 minutes) to reduce API calls. Study session data and AI time estimates are retained to improve your personal scheduling accuracy. You may request deletion of all your data at any time by contacting us.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Third-Party AI Processing</p>
            <p>Assignment titles, descriptions, and due dates are sent to Groq (<a href="https://groq.com" class="font-semibold text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800 transition-colors" target="_blank" rel="noopener">groq.com</a>) solely to generate time estimates. No personally identifiable information (name, email, school) is included in these requests. Groq's privacy policy applies to this processing.</p>
          </div>

          <div>
            <p class="font-bold text-slate-800 mb-1">Deletion Requests</p>
            <p>To request deletion of your account and all associated data, contact us at the email below. We will process deletion requests within 30 days.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="px-8 py-7">
        <h2 class="text-base font-extrabold text-slate-900 mb-2">Contact</h2>
        <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">Questions? Email <a href="mailto:jacetimm@gmail.com" class="font-semibold text-indigo-600 hover:text-indigo-800 transition-colors">jacetimm@gmail.com</a>.</p>
      </div>

    </div>

    <!-- Footer links -->
    <p class="mt-8 text-center text-xs text-slate-400">
      Also see our <%= link_to "Terms of Service", "/terms", class: "font-semibold text-slate-500 hover:text-indigo-600 underline underline-offset-2 transition-colors" %>.
    </p>

  </div>
</div>
